ode><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"PersistentArrayNCA/index.html\">PersistentArrayNCA</a></span><span>\u000A  (<a href=\"PersistentArrayNCA/argument-1-Config/index.html\">Config</a> : <a href=\"../Parameters/module-type-PERSISTENT_ARRAY_CONFIG/index.html\">Parameters.PERSISTENT_ARRAY_CONFIG</a>)\u000A  (<a href=\"PersistentArrayNCA/argument-2-Node/index.html\">Node</a> : <a href=\"../Parameters/module-type-NODE/index.html\">Parameters.NODE</a>) : \u000A  <a href=\"../Sig/module-type-UNION_FIND_LATTICE/index.html\">Sig.UNION_FIND_LATTICE</a> <span class=\"keyword\">with</span> <span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <a href=\"../Sig/module-type-UNION_FIND_LATTICE/index.html#type-node\">node</a> = <a href=\"PersistentArrayNCA/argument-2-Node/index.html#type-t\">Node.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Persistent array based union-find lattice. Same as <a href=\"PersistentArray/index.html\"><code>PersistentArray</code></a>, but builds <a href=\"../Sig/module-type-UNION_FIND_LATTICE/index.html#val-join\" title=\"Sig.UNION_FIND_LATTICE.join\"><code>join</code></a> on the nearest common ancestor instead of on one of the arguments.</p></div></div>"}